@evanchooly I started a Gradle plugin based on your Java client: https://github.com/vic-cw/openwhisk-gradle-plugin. Hope that makes you happy :)

@lordofthejars I also wanted to give you a heads up since you previously voiced the idea of such a tool.

Feel free to take a look at this first version. I would love to have your thoughts on it!

@rabbah @markusthoemmes @dgrove-oss 
Please look into this.
It's ready to merge.

@sven-lange-last 
>Wouldn't it be possible to work around this problem by setting invoker_runcdir: "/run/runc" in the Ansible environment for Jenkins?

Thank you for the suggestion, I will try it.

I have now bumped the version to current latest. Also to ensure some of the transitive dependencies from mesos-actor and s3 connector confirm to same version now [constraints](https://docs.gradle.org/4.10.2/userguide/managing_transitive_dependencies.html#sec:dependency_constraints) are placed to enforce that.

With these I do not see warning now

@dubee If needed then please run another PG

@rabbah This PR is now read to be merged!
